61 SlotIndex ----
62 InsertPointAnalysis::computeLastInsertPoint(const LiveInterval &CurLI, 0
63 const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { ----
64 unsigned Num = MBB.getNumber(); 0
65 std::pair &LIP = LastInsertPoint[Num]; 0
66 SlotIndex MBBEnd = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&MBB); 0
67 ----
68 SmallVector ExceptionalSuccessors; 0
69 bool EHPadSuccessor = false; 0
70 for (const MachineBasicBlock *SMBB : MBB.successors()) { 0
71 if (SMBB->isEHPad()) { 0
72 ExceptionalSuccessors.push_back(SMBB); 0
73 EHPadSuccessor = true; 0
74 } else if (SMBB->isInlineAsmBrIndirectTarget()) 0
75 ExceptionalSuccessors.push_back(SMBB); 0
76 } ----
77 ----
78 // Compute insert points on the first call. The pair is independent of the ----
79 // current live interval. ----
80 if (!LIP.first.isValid()) { 0
81 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator FirstTerm = MBB.getFirstTerminator(); 0
82 if (FirstTerm == MBB.end()) 0
83 LIP.first = MBBEnd; 0
84 else ----
85 LIP.first = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*FirstTerm); 0
86 ----
87 // If there is a landing pad or inlineasm_br successor, also find the ----
88 // instruction. If there is no such instruction, we don't need to do ----
89 // anything special. We assume there cannot be multiple instructions that ----
90 // are Calls with EHPad successors or INLINEASM_BR in a block. Further, we ----
91 // assume that if there are any, they will be after any other call ----
92 // instructions in the block. ----
93 if (ExceptionalSuccessors.empty()) 0
94 return LIP.first; 0
95 for (const MachineInstr &MI : llvm::reverse(MBB)) { 0
96 if ((EHPadSuccessor && MI.isCall()) || 0
97 MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::INLINEASM_BR) { 0
98 LIP.second = LIS.getInstructionIndex(MI); 0
99 break; 0
100 } ----
101 } ----
102 } ----
103 ----
104 // If CurLI is live into a landing pad successor, move the last insert point ----
105 // back to the call that may throw. ----
106 if (!LIP.second) 0
107 return LIP.first; 0
108 ----
109 if (none_of(ExceptionalSuccessors, [&](const MachineBasicBlock *EHPad) { 0
110 return LIS.isLiveInToMBB(CurLI, EHPad); 0
111 })) ----
112 return LIP.first; 0
113 ----
114 // Find the value leaving MBB. ----
115 const VNInfo *VNI = CurLI.getVNInfoBefore(MBBEnd); 0
116 if (!VNI) 0
117 return LIP.first; 0
118 ----
119 // The def of statepoint instruction is a gc relocation and it should be alive ----
120 // in landing pad. So we cannot split interval after statepoint instruction. ----
121 if (SlotIndex::isSameInstr(VNI->def, LIP.second)) 0
122 if (auto *I = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(LIP.second)) 0
123 if (I->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT) 0
124 return LIP.second; 0
125 ----
126 // If the value leaving MBB was defined after the call in MBB, it can't ----
127 // really be live-in to the landing pad. This can happen if the landing pad ----
128 // has a PHI, and this register is undef on the exceptional edge. ----
129 // ----
130 if (!SlotIndex::isEarlierInstr(VNI->def, LIP.second) && VNI->def < MBBEnd) 0
131 return LIP.first; 0
132 ----
133 // Value is properly live-in to the landing pad. ----
134 // Only allow inserts before the call. ----
135 return LIP.second; 0
136 } 0

139 InsertPointAnalysis::getLastInsertPointIter(const LiveInterval &CurLI, 0

142 if (LIP == LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&MBB)) 0
143 return MBB.end(); 0
144 return LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(LIP); 0
145 } ----

163 /// analyzeUses - Count instructions, basic blocks, and loops using CurLI. ----
164 void SplitAnalysis::analyzeUses() { 0
165 assert(UseSlots.empty() && "Call clear first"); 0
166 ----
167 // First get all the defs from the interval values. This provides the correct ----
168 // slots for early clobbers. ----
169 for (const VNInfo *VNI : CurLI->valnos) 0
170 if (!VNI->isPHIDef() && !VNI->isUnused()) 0
171 UseSlots.push_back(VNI->def); 0
172 ----
173 // Get use slots form the use-def chain. ----
174 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
175 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI.use_nodbg_operands(CurLI->reg())) 0
176 if (!MO.isUndef()) 0
177 UseSlots.push_back(LIS.getInstructionIndex(*MO.getParent()).getRegSlot()); 0
178 ----
179 array_pod_sort(UseSlots.begin(), UseSlots.end()); 0
180 ----
181 // Remove duplicates, keeping the smaller slot for each instruction. ----
182 // That is what we want for early clobbers. ----
183 UseSlots.erase(std::unique(UseSlots.begin(), UseSlots.end(), 0
184 SlotIndex::isSameInstr), ----
185 UseSlots.end()); 0
186 ----
187 // Compute per-live block info. ----
188 calcLiveBlockInfo(); 0
189 ----
190 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Analyze counted " << UseSlots.size() << " instrs in " 0
191 << UseBlocks.size() << " blocks, through " ----
192 << NumThroughBlocks << " blocks.\n"); ----
193 } 0
194 ----
195 /// calcLiveBlockInfo - Fill the LiveBlocks array with information about blocks ----
196 /// where CurLI is live. ----
197 void SplitAnalysis::calcLiveBlockInfo() { 0
198 ThroughBlocks.resize(MF.getNumBlockIDs()); 0
199 NumThroughBlocks = NumGapBlocks = 0; 0
200 if (CurLI->empty()) 0
201 return; 0
202 ----
203 LiveInterval::const_iterator LVI = CurLI->begin(); 0
204 LiveInterval::const_iterator LVE = CurLI->end(); 0
205 ----
206 SmallVectorImpl::const_iterator UseI, UseE; ----
207 UseI = UseSlots.begin(); 0
208 UseE = UseSlots.end(); 0
209 ----
210 // Loop over basic blocks where CurLI is live. ----
211 MachineFunction::iterator MFI = ----
212 LIS.getMBBFromIndex(LVI->start)->getIterator(); 0
213 while (true) { ----
214 BlockInfo BI; 0
215 BI.MBB = &*MFI; 0
216 SlotIndex Start, Stop; 0
217 std::tie(Start, Stop) = LIS.getSlotIndexes()->getMBBRange(BI.MBB); 0
218 ----
219 // If the block contains no uses, the range must be live through. At one ----
220 // point, RegisterCoalescer could create dangling ranges that ended ----
221 // mid-block. ----
222 if (UseI == UseE || *UseI >= Stop) { 0
223 ++NumThroughBlocks; 0
224 ThroughBlocks.set(BI.MBB->getNumber()); 0
225 // The range shouldn't end mid-block if there are no uses. This shouldn't ----
226 // happen. ----
227 assert(LVI->end >= Stop && "range ends mid block with no uses"); 0
228 } else { ----
229 // This block has uses. Find the first and last uses in the block. ----
230 BI.FirstInstr = *UseI; 0
231 assert(BI.FirstInstr >= Start); 0
232 do ++UseI; 0
233 while (UseI != UseE && *UseI < Stop); 0
234 BI.LastInstr = UseI[-1]; 0
235 assert(BI.LastInstr < Stop); 0
236 ----
237 // LVI is the first live segment overlapping MBB. ----
238 BI.LiveIn = LVI->start <= Start; 0
239 ----
240 // When not live in, the first use should be a def. ----
241 if (!BI.LiveIn) { 0
242 assert(LVI->start == LVI->valno->def && "Dangling Segment start"); 0
243 assert(LVI->start == BI.FirstInstr && "First instr should be a def"); 0
244 BI.FirstDef = BI.FirstInstr; 0
245 } ----
246 ----
247 // Look for gaps in the live range. ----
248 BI.LiveOut = true; 0
249 while (LVI->end < Stop) { 0
250 SlotIndex LastStop = LVI->end; 0
251 if (++LVI == LVE || LVI->start >= Stop) { 0
252 BI.LiveOut = false; 0
253 BI.LastInstr = LastStop; 0
254 break; 0
255 } ----
256 ----
257 if (LastStop < LVI->start) { 0
258 // There is a gap in the live range. Create duplicate entries for the ----
259 // live-in snippet and the live-out snippet. ----
260 ++NumGapBlocks; 0
261 ----
262 // Push the Live-in part. ----
263 BI.LiveOut = false; 0
264 UseBlocks.push_back(BI); 0
265 UseBlocks.back().LastInstr = LastStop; 0
266 ----
267 // Set up BI for the live-out part. ----
268 BI.LiveIn = false; 0
269 BI.LiveOut = true; 0
270 BI.FirstInstr = BI.FirstDef = LVI->start; 0
271 } ----
272 ----
273 // A Segment that starts in the middle of the block must be a def. ----
274 assert(LVI->start == LVI->valno->def && "Dangling Segment start"); 0
275 if (!BI.FirstDef) 0
276 BI.FirstDef = LVI->start; 0
277 } ----
278 ----
279 UseBlocks.push_back(BI); 0
280 ----
281 // LVI is now at LVE or LVI->end >= Stop. ----
282 if (LVI == LVE) 0
283 break; 0
284 } ----
285 ----
286 // Live segment ends exactly at Stop. Move to the next segment. ----
287 if (LVI->end == Stop && ++LVI == LVE) 0
288 break; 0
289 ----
290 // Pick the next basic block. ----
291 if (LVI->start < Stop) 0
292 ++MFI; 0
293 else ----
294 MFI = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(LVI->start)->getIterator(); 0
295 } 0
296 ----
297 assert(getNumLiveBlocks() == countLiveBlocks(CurLI) && "Bad block count"); 0
298 } ----
299 ----
300 unsigned SplitAnalysis::countLiveBlocks(const LiveInterval *cli) const { 0
301 if (cli->empty()) 0
302 return 0; 0
303 LiveInterval *li = const_cast(cli); 0
304 LiveInterval::iterator LVI = li->begin(); 0
305 LiveInterval::iterator LVE = li->end(); 0
306 unsigned Count = 0; 0
307 ----
308 // Loop over basic blocks where li is live. ----
309 MachineFunction::const_iterator MFI = ----
310 LIS.getMBBFromIndex(LVI->start)->getIterator(); 0
311 SlotIndex Stop = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&*MFI); 0
312 while (true) { ----
313 ++Count; 0
314 LVI = li->advanceTo(LVI, Stop); 0
315 if (LVI == LVE) 0
316 return Count; 0
317 do { ----
318 ++MFI; 0
319 Stop = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&*MFI); 0
320 } while (Stop <= LVI->start); 0
321 } ----
322 } ----
323 ----
324 bool SplitAnalysis::isOriginalEndpoint(SlotIndex Idx) const { 0
325 Register OrigReg = VRM.getOriginal(CurLI->reg()); 0
326 const LiveInterval &Orig = LIS.getInterval(OrigReg); 0
327 assert(!Orig.empty() && "Splitting empty interval?"); 0
328 LiveInterval::const_iterator I = Orig.find(Idx); 0
329 ----
330 // Range containing Idx should begin at Idx. ----
331 if (I != Orig.end() && I->start <= Idx) 0
332 return I->start == Idx; 0
333 ----
334 // Range does not contain Idx, previous must end at Idx. ----
335 return I != Orig.begin() && (--I)->end == Idx; 0
336 } ----

387 /// Find a subrange corresponding to the exact lane mask @p LM in the live ----
388 /// interval @p LI. The interval @p LI is assumed to contain such a subrange. ----
389 /// This function is used to find corresponding subranges between the ----
390 /// original interval and the new intervals. ----
391 template auto &getSubrangeImpl(LaneBitmask LM, T &LI) { 0
392 for (auto &S : LI.subranges()) 0
393 if (S.LaneMask == LM) 0
394 return S; 0
395 llvm_unreachable("SubRange for this mask not found"); 0
396 } ----

409 /// in the live interval @p LI. The interval @p LI is assumed to contain such ----
410 /// a subrange. This function is used to find corresponding subranges between ----

412 const LiveInterval::SubRange &getSubRangeForMask(LaneBitmask LM, 0
413 const LiveInterval &LI) { ----
414 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) 0
415 if ((S.LaneMask & LM) == LM) 0
416 return S; 0
417 llvm_unreachable("SubRange for this mask not found"); 0

420 void SplitEditor::addDeadDef(LiveInterval &LI, VNInfo *VNI, bool Original) { 0
421 if (!LI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
422 LI.createDeadDef(VNI); 0
423 return; 0
424 } ----
425 ----
426 SlotIndex Def = VNI->def; 0
427 if (Original) { 0
428 // If we are transferring a def from the original interval, make sure ----
429 // to only update the subranges for which the original subranges had ----
430 // a def at this location. ----
431 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
432 auto &PS = getSubRangeForMask(S.LaneMask, Edit->getParent()); 0
433 VNInfo *PV = PS.getVNInfoAt(Def); 0
434 if (PV != nullptr && PV->def == Def) 0
435 S.createDeadDef(Def, LIS.getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
436 } ----
437 } else { ----
438 // This is a new def: either from rematerialization, or from an inserted ----
439 // copy. Since rematerialization can regenerate a definition of a sub- ----
440 // register, we need to check which subranges need to be updated. ----
441 const MachineInstr *DefMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(Def); 0
442 assert(DefMI != nullptr); 0
443 LaneBitmask LM; 0
444 for (const MachineOperand &DefOp : DefMI->defs()) { 0
445 Register R = DefOp.getReg(); 0
446 if (R != LI.reg()) 0
447 continue; 0
448 if (unsigned SR = DefOp.getSubReg()) 0
449 LM |= TRI.getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SR); 0
450 else { ----
451 LM = MRI.getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(R); 0
452 break; 0
453 } ----
454 } ----
455 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) 0
456 if ((S.LaneMask & LM).any()) 0
457 S.createDeadDef(Def, LIS.getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
458 } ----
459 } ----

461 VNInfo *SplitEditor::defValue(unsigned RegIdx, 0
462 const VNInfo *ParentVNI, ----
463 SlotIndex Idx, ----
464 bool Original) { ----
465 assert(ParentVNI && "Mapping NULL value"); 0
466 assert(Idx.isValid() && "Invalid SlotIndex"); 0
467 assert(Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Idx) == ParentVNI && "Bad Parent VNI"); 0
468 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
469 ----
470 // Create a new value. ----
471 VNInfo *VNI = LI->getNextValue(Idx, LIS.getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
472 ----
473 bool Force = LI->hasSubRanges(); 0
474 ValueForcePair FP(Force ? nullptr : VNI, Force); 0
475 // Use insert for lookup, so we can add missing values with a second lookup. ----
476 std::pair InsP = ----
477 Values.insert(std::make_pair(std::make_pair(RegIdx, ParentVNI->id), FP)); 0
478 ----
479 // This was the first time (RegIdx, ParentVNI) was mapped, and it is not ----
480 // forced. Keep it as a simple def without any liveness. ----
481 if (!Force && InsP.second) 0
482 return VNI; 0
483 ----
484 // If the previous value was a simple mapping, add liveness for it now. ----
485 if (VNInfo *OldVNI = InsP.first->second.getPointer()) { 0
486 addDeadDef(*LI, OldVNI, Original); 0
487 ----
488 // No longer a simple mapping. Switch to a complex mapping. If the ----
489 // interval has subranges, make it a forced mapping. ----
490 InsP.first->second = ValueForcePair(nullptr, Force); 0
491 } ----
492 ----
493 // This is a complex mapping, add liveness for VNI ----
494 addDeadDef(*LI, VNI, Original); 0
495 return VNI; 0
496 } ----
497 ----
498 void SplitEditor::forceRecompute(unsigned RegIdx, const VNInfo &ParentVNI) { 0
499 ValueForcePair &VFP = Values[std::make_pair(RegIdx, ParentVNI.id)]; 0
500 VNInfo *VNI = VFP.getPointer(); 0
501 ----
502 // ParentVNI was either unmapped or already complex mapped. Either way, just ----
503 // set the force bit. ----
504 if (!VNI) { 0
505 VFP.setInt(true); 0
506 return; 0
507 } ----
508 ----
509 // This was previously a single mapping. Make sure the old def is represented ----
510 // by a trivial live range. ----
511 addDeadDef(LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)), VNI, false); 0
512 ----
513 // Mark as complex mapped, forced. ----
514 VFP = ValueForcePair(nullptr, true); 0
515 } ----

517 SlotIndex SplitEditor::buildSingleSubRegCopy(Register FromReg, Register ToReg, 0
518 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore, ----
519 unsigned SubIdx, LiveInterval &DestLI, bool Late, SlotIndex Def) { ----
520 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = TII.get(TargetOpcode::COPY); 0
521 bool FirstCopy = !Def.isValid(); 0
522 MachineInstr *CopyMI = BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DebugLoc(), Desc) 0
523 .addReg(ToReg, RegState::Define | getUndefRegState(FirstCopy) 0
524 | getInternalReadRegState(!FirstCopy), SubIdx) 0
525 .addReg(FromReg, 0, SubIdx); 0
526 ----
527 SlotIndexes &Indexes = *LIS.getSlotIndexes(); 0
528 if (FirstCopy) { 0
529 Def = Indexes.insertMachineInstrInMaps(*CopyMI, Late).getRegSlot(); 0
530 } else { ----
531 CopyMI->bundleWithPred(); 0
532 } ----
533 return Def; 0
534 } ----
535 ----
536 SlotIndex SplitEditor::buildCopy(Register FromReg, Register ToReg, 0
537 LaneBitmask LaneMask, MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
538 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore, bool Late, unsigned RegIdx) { ----
539 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = TII.get(TargetOpcode::COPY); 0
540 SlotIndexes &Indexes = *LIS.getSlotIndexes(); 0
541 if (LaneMask.all() || LaneMask == MRI.getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(FromReg)) { 0
542 // The full vreg is copied. ----
543 MachineInstr *CopyMI = ----
544 BuildMI(MBB, InsertBefore, DebugLoc(), Desc, ToReg).addReg(FromReg); 0
545 return Indexes.insertMachineInstrInMaps(*CopyMI, Late).getRegSlot(); 0
546 } ----
547 ----
548 // Only a subset of lanes needs to be copied. The following is a simple ----
549 // heuristic to construct a sequence of COPYs. We could add a target ----
550 // specific callback if this turns out to be suboptimal. ----
551 LiveInterval &DestLI = LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
552 ----
553 // First pass: Try to find a perfectly matching subregister index. If none ----
554 // exists find the one covering the most lanemask bits. ----
555 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI.getRegClass(FromReg); 0
556 assert(RC == MRI.getRegClass(ToReg) && "Should have same reg class"); 0
557 ----
558 SmallVector SubIndexes; 0
559 ----
560 // Abort if we cannot possibly implement the COPY with the given indexes. ----
561 if (!TRI.getCoveringSubRegIndexes(MRI, RC, LaneMask, SubIndexes)) 0
562 report_fatal_error("Impossible to implement partial COPY"); 0
563 ----
564 SlotIndex Def; 0
565 for (unsigned BestIdx : SubIndexes) { 0
566 Def = buildSingleSubRegCopy(FromReg, ToReg, MBB, InsertBefore, BestIdx, 0
567 DestLI, Late, Def); ----
568 } ----
569 ----
570 BumpPtrAllocator &Allocator = LIS.getVNInfoAllocator(); 0
571 DestLI.refineSubRanges( 0
572 Allocator, LaneMask, ----
573 [Def, &Allocator](LiveInterval::SubRange &SR) { 0
574 SR.createDeadDef(Def, Allocator); 0
575 }, 0
576 Indexes, TRI); ----
577 ----
578 return Def; 0
579 } 0

581 VNInfo *SplitEditor::defFromParent(unsigned RegIdx, const VNInfo *ParentVNI, 0
582 SlotIndex UseIdx, MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
583 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I) { ----
584 SlotIndex Def; 0
585 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
586 ----
587 // We may be trying to avoid interference that ends at a deleted instruction, ----
588 // so always begin RegIdx 0 early and all others late. ----
589 bool Late = RegIdx != 0; 0
590 ----
591 // Attempt cheap-as-a-copy rematerialization. ----
592 Register Original = VRM.getOriginal(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
593 LiveInterval &OrigLI = LIS.getInterval(Original); 0
594 VNInfo *OrigVNI = OrigLI.getVNInfoAt(UseIdx); 0
595 ----
596 Register Reg = LI->reg(); 0
597 bool DidRemat = false; 0
598 if (OrigVNI) { 0
599 LiveRangeEdit::Remat RM(ParentVNI); 0
600 RM.OrigMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(OrigVNI->def); 0
601 if (Edit->canRematerializeAt(RM, OrigVNI, UseIdx, true)) { 0
602 Def = Edit->rematerializeAt(MBB, I, Reg, RM, TRI, Late); 0
603 ++NumRemats; 0
604 DidRemat = true; 0
605 } ----
606 } ----
607 if (!DidRemat) { 0
608 LaneBitmask LaneMask; 0
609 if (OrigLI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
610 LaneMask = LaneBitmask::getNone(); 0
611 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : OrigLI.subranges()) { 0
612 if (S.liveAt(UseIdx)) 0
613 LaneMask |= S.LaneMask; 0
614 } ----
615 } else { ----
616 LaneMask = LaneBitmask::getAll(); 0
617 } ----
618 ----
619 if (LaneMask.none()) { 0
620 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = TII.get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF); 0
621 MachineInstr *ImplicitDef = BuildMI(MBB, I, DebugLoc(), Desc, Reg); 0
622 SlotIndexes &Indexes = *LIS.getSlotIndexes(); 0
623 Def = Indexes.insertMachineInstrInMaps(*ImplicitDef, Late).getRegSlot(); 0
624 } else { ----
625 ++NumCopies; 0
626 Def = buildCopy(Edit->getReg(), Reg, LaneMask, MBB, I, Late, RegIdx); 0
627 } ----
628 } ----
629 ----
630 // Define the value in Reg. ----
631 return defValue(RegIdx, ParentVNI, Def, false); 0
632 } ----
633 ----
634 /// Create a new virtual register and live interval. ----
635 unsigned SplitEditor::openIntv() { 0
636 // Create the complement as index 0. ----
637 if (Edit->empty()) 0
638 Edit->createEmptyInterval(); 0
639 ----
640 // Create the open interval. ----
641 OpenIdx = Edit->size(); 0
642 Edit->createEmptyInterval(); 0
643 return OpenIdx; 0
644 } ----
645 ----
646 void SplitEditor::selectIntv(unsigned Idx) { 0
647 assert(Idx != 0 && "Cannot select the complement interval"); 0
648 assert(Idx < Edit->size() && "Can only select previously opened interval"); 0
649 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " selectIntv " << OpenIdx << " -> " << Idx << '\n'); 0
650 OpenIdx = Idx; 0
651 } 0
652 ----
653 SlotIndex SplitEditor::enterIntvBefore(SlotIndex Idx) { 0
654 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before enterIntvBefore"); 0
655 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " enterIntvBefore " << Idx); 0
656 Idx = Idx.getBaseIndex(); 0
657 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Idx); 0
658 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
659 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": not live\n"); 0
660 return Idx; 0
661 } ----
662 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": valno " << ParentVNI->id << '\n'); 0
663 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(Idx); 0
664 assert(MI && "enterIntvBefore called with invalid index"); 0
665 ----
666 VNInfo *VNI = defFromParent(OpenIdx, ParentVNI, Idx, *MI->getParent(), MI); 0
667 return VNI->def; 0
668 } ----
669 ----
670 SlotIndex SplitEditor::enterIntvAfter(SlotIndex Idx) { 0
671 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before enterIntvAfter"); 0
672 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " enterIntvAfter " << Idx); 0
673 Idx = Idx.getBoundaryIndex(); 0
674 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Idx); 0
675 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
676 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": not live\n"); 0
677 return Idx; 0
678 } ----
679 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": valno " << ParentVNI->id << '\n'); 0
680 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(Idx); 0
681 assert(MI && "enterIntvAfter called with invalid index"); 0
682 ----
683 VNInfo *VNI = defFromParent(OpenIdx, ParentVNI, Idx, *MI->getParent(), 0
684 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI))); ----
685 return VNI->def; 0
686 } ----
687 ----
688 SlotIndex SplitEditor::enterIntvAtEnd(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
689 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before enterIntvAtEnd"); 0
690 SlotIndex End = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&MBB); 0
691 SlotIndex Last = End.getPrevSlot(); 0
692 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " enterIntvAtEnd " << printMBBReference(MBB) << ", " 0
693 << Last); ----
694 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Last); 0
695 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
696 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": not live\n"); 0
697 return End; 0
698 } ----
699 SlotIndex LSP = SA.getLastSplitPoint(&MBB); 0
700 if (LSP < Last) { 0
701 // It could be that the use after LSP is a def, and thus the ParentVNI ----
702 // just selected starts at that def. For this case to exist, the def ----
703 // must be part of a tied def/use pair (as otherwise we'd have split ----
704 // distinct live ranges into individual live intervals), and thus we ----
705 // can insert the def into the VNI of the use and the tied def/use ----
706 // pair can live in the resulting interval. ----
707 Last = LSP; 0
708 ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Last); 0
709 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
710 // undef use --> undef tied def ----
711 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": tied use not live\n"); 0
712 return End; 0
713 } ----
714 } ----
715 ----
716 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": valno " << ParentVNI->id); 0
717 VNInfo *VNI = defFromParent(OpenIdx, ParentVNI, Last, MBB, 0
718 SA.getLastSplitPointIter(&MBB)); 0
719 RegAssign.insert(VNI->def, End, OpenIdx); 0
720 LLVM_DEBUG(dump()); 0
721 return VNI->def; 0
722 } ----
723 ----
724 /// useIntv - indicate that all instructions in MBB should use OpenLI. ----
725 void SplitEditor::useIntv(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
726 useIntv(LIS.getMBBStartIdx(&MBB), LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&MBB)); 0
727 } 0
728 ----
729 void SplitEditor::useIntv(SlotIndex Start, SlotIndex End) { 0
730 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before useIntv"); 0
731 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " useIntv [" << Start << ';' << End << "):"); 0
732 RegAssign.insert(Start, End, OpenIdx); 0
733 LLVM_DEBUG(dump()); 0
734 } 0
735 ----
736 SlotIndex SplitEditor::leaveIntvAfter(SlotIndex Idx) { 0
737 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before leaveIntvAfter"); 0
738 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " leaveIntvAfter " << Idx); 0
739 ----
740 // The interval must be live beyond the instruction at Idx. ----
741 SlotIndex Boundary = Idx.getBoundaryIndex(); 0
742 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Boundary); 0
743 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
744 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": not live\n"); 0
745 return Boundary.getNextSlot(); 0
746 } ----
747 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": valno " << ParentVNI->id << '\n'); 0
748 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(Boundary); 0
749 assert(MI && "No instruction at index"); 0
750 ----
751 // In spill mode, make live ranges as short as possible by inserting the copy ----
752 // before MI. This is only possible if that instruction doesn't redefine the ----
753 // value. The inserted COPY is not a kill, and we don't need to recompute ----
754 // the source live range. The spiller also won't try to hoist this copy. ----
755 if (SpillMode && !SlotIndex::isSameInstr(ParentVNI->def, Idx) && 0
756 MI->readsVirtualRegister(Edit->getReg())) { 0
757 forceRecompute(0, *ParentVNI); 0
758 defFromParent(0, ParentVNI, Idx, *MI->getParent(), MI); 0
759 return Idx; 0
760 } ----
761 ----
762 VNInfo *VNI = defFromParent(0, ParentVNI, Boundary, *MI->getParent(), 0
763 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI))); ----
764 return VNI->def; 0
765 } ----
766 ----
767 SlotIndex SplitEditor::leaveIntvBefore(SlotIndex Idx) { 0
768 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before leaveIntvBefore"); 0
769 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " leaveIntvBefore " << Idx); 0
770 ----
771 // The interval must be live into the instruction at Idx. ----
772 Idx = Idx.getBaseIndex(); 0
773 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Idx); 0
774 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
775 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": not live\n"); 0
776 return Idx.getNextSlot(); 0
777 } ----
778 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": valno " << ParentVNI->id << '\n'); 0
779 ----
780 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(Idx); 0
781 assert(MI && "No instruction at index"); 0
782 VNInfo *VNI = defFromParent(0, ParentVNI, Idx, *MI->getParent(), MI); 0
783 return VNI->def; 0
784 } ----
785 ----
786 SlotIndex SplitEditor::leaveIntvAtTop(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
787 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before leaveIntvAtTop"); 0
788 SlotIndex Start = LIS.getMBBStartIdx(&MBB); 0
789 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " leaveIntvAtTop " << printMBBReference(MBB) << ", " 0
790 << Start); ----
791 ----
792 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Start); 0
793 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
794 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ": not live\n"); 0
795 return Start; 0
796 } ----
797 ----
798 VNInfo *VNI = defFromParent(0, ParentVNI, Start, MBB, 0
799 MBB.SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug(MBB.begin())); ----
800 RegAssign.insert(Start, VNI->def, OpenIdx); 0
801 LLVM_DEBUG(dump()); 0
802 return VNI->def; 0
803 } ----
804 ----
805 static bool hasTiedUseOf(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned Reg) { 0
806 return any_of(MI.defs(), [Reg](const MachineOperand &MO) { 0
807 return MO.isReg() && MO.isTied() && MO.getReg() == Reg; 0
808 }); 0
809 } ----
810 ----
811 void SplitEditor::overlapIntv(SlotIndex Start, SlotIndex End) { 0
812 assert(OpenIdx && "openIntv not called before overlapIntv"); 0
813 const VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Start); 0
814 assert(ParentVNI == Edit->getParent().getVNInfoBefore(End) && 0
815 "Parent changes value in extended range"); ----
816 assert(LIS.getMBBFromIndex(Start) == LIS.getMBBFromIndex(End) && 0
817 "Range cannot span basic blocks"); ----
818 ----
819 // The complement interval will be extended as needed by LICalc.extend(). ----
820 if (ParentVNI) 0
821 forceRecompute(0, *ParentVNI); 0
822 ----
823 // If the last use is tied to a def, we can't mark it as live for the ----
824 // interval which includes only the use. That would cause the tied pair ----
825 // to end up in two different intervals. ----
826 if (auto *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(End)) 0
827 if (hasTiedUseOf(*MI, Edit->getReg())) { 0
828 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "skip overlap due to tied def at end\n"); 0
829 return; 0
830 } ----
831 ----
832 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " overlapIntv [" << Start << ';' << End << "):"); 0
833 RegAssign.insert(Start, End, OpenIdx); 0
834 LLVM_DEBUG(dump()); 0
835 } ----
836 ----
837 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
838 // Spill modes ----
839 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
840 ----
841 void SplitEditor::removeBackCopies(SmallVectorImpl &Copies) { 0
842 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(0)); 0
843 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removing " << Copies.size() << " back-copies.\n"); 0
844 RegAssignMap::iterator AssignI; 0
845 AssignI.setMap(RegAssign); 0
846 ----
847 for (const VNInfo *C : Copies) { 0
848 SlotIndex Def = C->def; 0
849 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(Def); 0
850 assert(MI && "No instruction for back-copy"); 0
851 ----
852 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
853 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI(MI); 0
854 bool AtBegin; ----
855 do AtBegin = MBBI == MBB->begin(); 0
856 while (!AtBegin && (--MBBI)->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()); 0
857 ----
858 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removing " << Def << '\t' << *MI); 0
859 LIS.removeVRegDefAt(*LI, Def); 0
860 LIS.RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(*MI); 0
861 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
862 ----
863 // Adjust RegAssign if a register assignment is killed at Def. We want to ----
864 // avoid calculating the live range of the source register if possible. ----
865 AssignI.find(Def.getPrevSlot()); 0
866 if (!AssignI.valid() || AssignI.start() >= Def) 0
867 continue; 0
868 // If MI doesn't kill the assigned register, just leave it. ----
869 if (AssignI.stop() != Def) 0
870 continue; 0
871 unsigned RegIdx = AssignI.value(); 0
872 // We could hoist back-copy right after another back-copy. As a result ----
873 // MMBI points to copy instruction which is actually dead now. ----
874 // We cannot set its stop to MBBI which will be the same as start and ----
875 // interval does not support that. ----
876 SlotIndex Kill = ----
877 AtBegin ? SlotIndex() : LIS.getInstructionIndex(*MBBI).getRegSlot(); 0
878 if (AtBegin || !MBBI->readsVirtualRegister(Edit->getReg()) || 0
879 Kill <= AssignI.start()) { 0
880 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " cannot find simple kill of RegIdx " << RegIdx 0
881 << '\n'); ----
882 forceRecompute(RegIdx, *Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(Def)); 0
883 } else { ----
884 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " move kill to " << Kill << '\t' << *MBBI); 0
885 AssignI.setStop(Kill); 0
886 } ----
887 } ----
888 } 0
889 ----
890 MachineBasicBlock* ----
891 SplitEditor::findShallowDominator(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
892 MachineBasicBlock *DefMBB) { ----
893 if (MBB == DefMBB) 0
894 return MBB; 0
895 assert(MDT.dominates(DefMBB, MBB) && "MBB must be dominated by the def."); 0
896 ----
897 const MachineLoopInfo &Loops = SA.Loops; 0
898 const MachineLoop *DefLoop = Loops.getLoopFor(DefMBB); 0
899 MachineDomTreeNode *DefDomNode = MDT[DefMBB]; 0
900 ----
901 // Best candidate so far. ----
902 MachineBasicBlock *BestMBB = MBB; 0
903 unsigned BestDepth = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
904 ----
905 while (true) { ----
906 const MachineLoop *Loop = Loops.getLoopFor(MBB); 0
907 ----
908 // MBB isn't in a loop, it doesn't get any better. All dominators have a ----
909 // higher frequency by definition. ----
910 if (!Loop) { 0
911 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Def in " << printMBBReference(*DefMBB) 0
912 << " dominates " << printMBBReference(*MBB) ----
913 << " at depth 0\n"); ----
914 return MBB; 0
915 } ----
916 ----
917 // We'll never be able to exit the DefLoop. ----
918 if (Loop == DefLoop) { 0
919 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Def in " << printMBBReference(*DefMBB) 0
920 << " dominates " << printMBBReference(*MBB) ----
921 << " in the same loop\n"); ----
922 return MBB; 0
923 } ----
924 ----
925 // Least busy dominator seen so far. ----
926 unsigned Depth = Loop->getLoopDepth(); 0
927 if (Depth < BestDepth) { 0
928 BestMBB = MBB; 0
929 BestDepth = Depth; 0
930 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Def in " << printMBBReference(*DefMBB) 0
931 << " dominates " << printMBBReference(*MBB) ----
932 << " at depth " << Depth << '\n'); ----
933 } ----
934 ----
935 // Leave loop by going to the immediate dominator of the loop header. ----
936 // This is a bigger stride than simply walking up the dominator tree. ----
937 MachineDomTreeNode *IDom = MDT[Loop->getHeader()]->getIDom(); 0
938 ----
939 // Too far up the dominator tree? ----
940 if (!IDom || !MDT.dominates(DefDomNode, IDom)) 0
941 return BestMBB; 0
942 ----
943 MBB = IDom->getBlock(); 0
944 } 0
945 } ----
946 ----
947 void SplitEditor::computeRedundantBackCopies( 0
948 DenseSet &NotToHoistSet, SmallVectorImpl &BackCopies) { ----
949 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(0)); 0
950 const LiveInterval *Parent = &Edit->getParent(); 0
951 SmallVector, 8> EqualVNs(Parent->getNumValNums()); 0
952 SmallPtrSet DominatedVNIs; 0
953 ----
954 // Aggregate VNIs having the same value as ParentVNI. ----
955 for (VNInfo *VNI : LI->valnos) { 0
956 if (VNI->isUnused()) 0
957 continue; 0
958 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(VNI->def); 0
959 EqualVNs[ParentVNI->id].insert(VNI); 0
960 } ----
961 ----
962 // For VNI aggregation of each ParentVNI, collect dominated, i.e., ----
963 // redundant VNIs to BackCopies. ----
964 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Parent->getNumValNums(); i != e; ++i) { 0
965 const VNInfo *ParentVNI = Parent->getValNumInfo(i); 0
966 if (!NotToHoistSet.count(ParentVNI->id)) 0
967 continue; 0
968 SmallPtrSetIterator It1 = EqualVNs[ParentVNI->id].begin(); 0
969 SmallPtrSetIterator It2 = It1; 0
970 for (; It1 != EqualVNs[ParentVNI->id].end(); ++It1) { 0
971 It2 = It1; 0
972 for (++It2; It2 != EqualVNs[ParentVNI->id].end(); ++It2) { 0
973 if (DominatedVNIs.count(*It1) || DominatedVNIs.count(*It2)) 0
974 continue; 0
975 ----
976 MachineBasicBlock *MBB1 = LIS.getMBBFromIndex((*It1)->def); 0
977 MachineBasicBlock *MBB2 = LIS.getMBBFromIndex((*It2)->def); 0
978 if (MBB1 == MBB2) { 0
979 DominatedVNIs.insert((*It1)->def < (*It2)->def ? (*It2) : (*It1)); 0
980 } else if (MDT.dominates(MBB1, MBB2)) { 0
981 DominatedVNIs.insert(*It2); 0
982 } else if (MDT.dominates(MBB2, MBB1)) { 0
983 DominatedVNIs.insert(*It1); 0
984 } ----
985 } ----
986 } ----
987 if (!DominatedVNIs.empty()) { 0
988 forceRecompute(0, *ParentVNI); 0
989 append_range(BackCopies, DominatedVNIs); 0
990 DominatedVNIs.clear(); 0
991 } ----
992 } ----
993 } 0
994 ----
995 /// For SM_Size mode, find a common dominator for all the back-copies for ----
996 /// the same ParentVNI and hoist the backcopies to the dominator BB. ----
997 /// For SM_Speed mode, if the common dominator is hot and it is not beneficial ----
998 /// to do the hoisting, simply remove the dominated backcopies for the same ----
999 /// ParentVNI. ----
1000 void SplitEditor::hoistCopies() { 0
1001 // Get the complement interval, always RegIdx 0. ----
1002 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(0)); 0
1003 const LiveInterval *Parent = &Edit->getParent(); 0
1004 ----
1005 // Track the nearest common dominator for all back-copies for each ParentVNI, ----
1006 // indexed by ParentVNI->id. ----
1007 using DomPair = std::pair; ----
1008 SmallVector NearestDom(Parent->getNumValNums()); 0
1009 // The total cost of all the back-copies for each ParentVNI. ----
1010 SmallVector Costs(Parent->getNumValNums()); 0
1011 // The ParentVNI->id set for which hoisting back-copies are not beneficial ----
1012 // for Speed. ----
1013 DenseSet NotToHoistSet; 0
1014 ----
1015 // Find the nearest common dominator for parent values with multiple ----
1016 // back-copies. If a single back-copy dominates, put it in DomPair.second. ----
1017 for (VNInfo *VNI : LI->valnos) { 0
1018 if (VNI->isUnused()) 0
1019 continue; 0
1020 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(VNI->def); 0
1021 assert(ParentVNI && "Parent not live at complement def"); 0
1022 ----
1023 // Don't hoist remats. The complement is probably going to disappear ----
1024 // completely anyway. ----
1025 if (Edit->didRematerialize(ParentVNI)) 0
1026 continue; 0
1027 ----
1028 MachineBasicBlock *ValMBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
1029 ----
1030 DomPair &Dom = NearestDom[ParentVNI->id]; 0
1031 ----
1032 // Keep directly defined parent values. This is either a PHI or an ----
1033 // instruction in the complement range. All other copies of ParentVNI ----
1034 // should be eliminated. ----
1035 if (VNI->def == ParentVNI->def) { 0
1036 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Direct complement def at " << VNI->def << '\n'); 0
1037 Dom = DomPair(ValMBB, VNI->def); 0
1038 continue; 0
1039 } ----
1040 // Skip the singly mapped values. There is nothing to gain from hoisting a ----
1041 // single back-copy. ----
1042 if (Values.lookup(std::make_pair(0, ParentVNI->id)).getPointer()) { 0
1043 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Single complement def at " << VNI->def << '\n'); 0
1044 continue; 0
1045 } ----
1046 ----
1047 if (!Dom.first) { 0
1048 // First time we see ParentVNI. VNI dominates itself. ----
1049 Dom = DomPair(ValMBB, VNI->def); 0
1050 } else if (Dom.first == ValMBB) { 0
1051 // Two defs in the same block. Pick the earlier def. ----
1052 if (!Dom.second.isValid() || VNI->def < Dom.second) 0
1053 Dom.second = VNI->def; 0
1054 } else { ----
1055 // Different basic blocks. Check if one dominates. ----
1056 MachineBasicBlock *Near = ----
1057 MDT.findNearestCommonDominator(Dom.first, ValMBB); 0
1058 if (Near == ValMBB) 0
1059 // Def ValMBB dominates. ----
1060 Dom = DomPair(ValMBB, VNI->def); 0
1061 else if (Near != Dom.first) 0
1062 // None dominate. Hoist to common dominator, need new def. ----
1063 Dom = DomPair(Near, SlotIndex()); 0
1064 Costs[ParentVNI->id] += MBFI.getBlockFreq(ValMBB); 0
1065 } ----
1066 ----
1067 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Multi-mapped complement " << VNI->id << '@' 0
1068 << VNI->def << " for parent " << ParentVNI->id << '@' ----
1069 << ParentVNI->def << " hoist to " ----
1070 << printMBBReference(*Dom.first) << ' ' << Dom.second ----
1071 << '\n'); ----
1072 } ----
1073 ----
1074 // Insert the hoisted copies. ----
1075 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Parent->getNumValNums(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1076 DomPair &Dom = NearestDom[i]; 0
1077 if (!Dom.first || Dom.second.isValid()) 0
1078 continue; 0
1079 // This value needs a hoisted copy inserted at the end of Dom.first. ----
1080 const VNInfo *ParentVNI = Parent->getValNumInfo(i); 0
1081 MachineBasicBlock *DefMBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(ParentVNI->def); 0
1082 // Get a less loopy dominator than Dom.first. ----
1083 Dom.first = findShallowDominator(Dom.first, DefMBB); 0
1084 if (SpillMode == SM_Speed && 0
1085 MBFI.getBlockFreq(Dom.first) > Costs[ParentVNI->id]) { 0
1086 NotToHoistSet.insert(ParentVNI->id); 0
1087 continue; 0
1088 } ----
1089 SlotIndex LSP = SA.getLastSplitPoint(Dom.first); 0
1090 if (LSP <= ParentVNI->def) { 0
1091 NotToHoistSet.insert(ParentVNI->id); 0
1092 continue; 0
1093 } ----
1094 Dom.second = defFromParent(0, ParentVNI, LSP, *Dom.first, 0
1095 SA.getLastSplitPointIter(Dom.first))->def; 0
1096 } ----
1097 ----
1098 // Remove redundant back-copies that are now known to be dominated by another ----
1099 // def with the same value. ----
1100 SmallVector BackCopies; 0
1101 for (VNInfo *VNI : LI->valnos) { 0
1102 if (VNI->isUnused()) 0
1103 continue; 0
1104 VNInfo *ParentVNI = Edit->getParent().getVNInfoAt(VNI->def); 0
1105 const DomPair &Dom = NearestDom[ParentVNI->id]; 0
1106 if (!Dom.first || Dom.second == VNI->def || 0
1107 NotToHoistSet.count(ParentVNI->id)) 0
1108 continue; 0
1109 BackCopies.push_back(VNI); 0
1110 forceRecompute(0, *ParentVNI); 0
1111 } ----
1112 ----
1113 // If it is not beneficial to hoist all the BackCopies, simply remove ----
1114 // redundant BackCopies in speed mode. ----
1115 if (SpillMode == SM_Speed && !NotToHoistSet.empty()) 0
1116 computeRedundantBackCopies(NotToHoistSet, BackCopies); 0
1117 ----
1118 removeBackCopies(BackCopies); 0
1119 } 0
1120 ----
1121 /// transferValues - Transfer all possible values to the new live ranges. ----
1122 /// Values that were rematerialized are left alone, they need LICalc.extend(). ----
1123 bool SplitEditor::transferValues() { 0
1124 bool Skipped = false; 0
1125 RegAssignMap::const_iterator AssignI = RegAssign.begin(); 0
1126 for (const LiveRange::Segment &S : Edit->getParent()) { 0
1127 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " blit " << S << ':'); 0
1128 VNInfo *ParentVNI = S.valno; 0
1129 // RegAssign has holes where RegIdx 0 should be used. ----
1130 SlotIndex Start = S.start; 0
1131 AssignI.advanceTo(Start); 0
1132 do { ----
1133 unsigned RegIdx; ----
1134 SlotIndex End = S.end; 0
1135 if (!AssignI.valid()) { 0
1136 RegIdx = 0; 0
1137 } else if (AssignI.start() <= Start) { 0
1138 RegIdx = AssignI.value(); 0
1139 if (AssignI.stop() < End) { 0
1140 End = AssignI.stop(); 0
1141 ++AssignI; 0
1142 } ----
1143 } else { ----
1144 RegIdx = 0; 0
1145 End = std::min(End, AssignI.start()); 0
1146 } ----
1147 ----
1148 // The interval [Start;End) is continuously mapped to RegIdx, ParentVNI. ----
1149 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " [" << Start << ';' << End << ")=" << RegIdx << '(' 0
1150 << printReg(Edit->get(RegIdx)) << ')'); ----
1151 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
1152 ----
1153 // Check for a simply defined value that can be blitted directly. ----
1154 ValueForcePair VFP = Values.lookup(std::make_pair(RegIdx, ParentVNI->id)); 0
1155 if (VNInfo *VNI = VFP.getPointer()) { 0
1156 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ':' << VNI->id); 0
1157 LI.addSegment(LiveInterval::Segment(Start, End, VNI)); 0
1158 Start = End; 0
1159 continue; 0
1160 } ----
1161 ----
1162 // Skip values with forced recomputation. ----
1163 if (VFP.getInt()) { 0
1164 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "(recalc)"); 0
1165 Skipped = true; 0
1166 Start = End; 0
1167 continue; 0
1168 } ----
1169 ----
1170 LiveIntervalCalc &LIC = getLICalc(RegIdx); 0
1171 ----
1172 // This value has multiple defs in RegIdx, but it wasn't rematerialized, ----
1173 // so the live range is accurate. Add live-in blocks in [Start;End) to the ----
1174 // LiveInBlocks. ----
1175 MachineFunction::iterator MBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(Start)->getIterator(); 0
1176 SlotIndex BlockStart, BlockEnd; 0
1177 std::tie(BlockStart, BlockEnd) = LIS.getSlotIndexes()->getMBBRange(&*MBB); 0
1178 ----
1179 // The first block may be live-in, or it may have its own def. ----
1180 if (Start != BlockStart) { 0
1181 VNInfo *VNI = LI.extendInBlock(BlockStart, std::min(BlockEnd, End)); 0
1182 assert(VNI && "Missing def for complex mapped value"); 0
1183 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ':' << VNI->id << "*" << printMBBReference(*MBB)); 0
1184 // MBB has its own def. Is it also live-out? ----
1185 if (BlockEnd <= End) 0
1186 LIC.setLiveOutValue(&*MBB, VNI); 0
1187 ----
1188 // Skip to the next block for live-in. ----
1189 ++MBB; 0
1190 BlockStart = BlockEnd; 0
1191 } ----
1192 ----
1193 // Handle the live-in blocks covered by [Start;End). ----
1194 assert(Start <= BlockStart && "Expected live-in block"); 0
1195 while (BlockStart < End) { 0
1196 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ">" << printMBBReference(*MBB)); 0
1197 BlockEnd = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&*MBB); 0
1198 if (BlockStart == ParentVNI->def) { 0
1199 // This block has the def of a parent PHI, so it isn't live-in. ----
1200 assert(ParentVNI->isPHIDef() && "Non-phi defined at block start?"); 0
1201 VNInfo *VNI = LI.extendInBlock(BlockStart, std::min(BlockEnd, End)); 0
1202 assert(VNI && "Missing def for complex mapped parent PHI"); 0
1203 if (End >= BlockEnd) 0
1204 LIC.setLiveOutValue(&*MBB, VNI); // Live-out as well. 0
1205 } else { ----
1206 // This block needs a live-in value. The last block covered may not ----
1207 // be live-out. ----
1208 if (End < BlockEnd) 0
1209 LIC.addLiveInBlock(LI, MDT[&*MBB], End); 0
1210 else { ----
1211 // Live-through, and we don't know the value. ----
1212 LIC.addLiveInBlock(LI, MDT[&*MBB]); 0
1213 LIC.setLiveOutValue(&*MBB, nullptr); 0
1214 } ----
1215 } ----
1216 BlockStart = BlockEnd; 0
1217 ++MBB; 0
1218 } ----
1219 Start = End; 0
1220 } while (Start != S.end); 0
1221 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << '\n'); 0
1222 } ----
1223 ----
1224 LICalc[0].calculateValues(); 0
1225 if (SpillMode) 0
1226 LICalc[1].calculateValues(); 0
1227 ----
1228 return Skipped; 0
1229 } 0
1230 ----
1231 static bool removeDeadSegment(SlotIndex Def, LiveRange &LR) { 0
1232 const LiveRange::Segment *Seg = LR.getSegmentContaining(Def); 0
1233 if (Seg == nullptr) 0
1234 return true; 0
1235 if (Seg->end != Def.getDeadSlot()) 0
1236 return false; 0
1237 // This is a dead PHI. Remove it. ----
1238 LR.removeSegment(*Seg, true); 0
1239 return true; 0
1240 } ----
1241 ----
1242 void SplitEditor::extendPHIRange(MachineBasicBlock &B, LiveIntervalCalc &LIC, 0
1243 LiveRange &LR, LaneBitmask LM, ----
1244 ArrayRef Undefs) { ----
1245 for (MachineBasicBlock *P : B.predecessors()) { 0
1246 SlotIndex End = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(P); 0
1247 SlotIndex LastUse = End.getPrevSlot(); 0
1248 // The predecessor may not have a live-out value. That is OK, like an ----
1249 // undef PHI operand. ----
1250 const LiveInterval &PLI = Edit->getParent(); 0
1251 // Need the cast because the inputs to ?: would otherwise be deemed ----
1252 // "incompatible": SubRange vs LiveInterval. ----
1253 const LiveRange &PSR = !LM.all() ? getSubRangeForMaskExact(LM, PLI) 0
1254 : static_cast(PLI); 0
1255 if (PSR.liveAt(LastUse)) 0
1256 LIC.extend(LR, End, /*PhysReg=*/0, Undefs); 0
1257 } ----
1258 } 0
1259 ----
1260 void SplitEditor::extendPHIKillRanges() { 0
1261 // Extend live ranges to be live-out for successor PHI values. ----
1262 ----
1263 // Visit each PHI def slot in the parent live interval. If the def is dead, ----
1264 // remove it. Otherwise, extend the live interval to reach the end indexes ----
1265 // of all predecessor blocks. ----
1266 ----
1267 const LiveInterval &ParentLI = Edit->getParent(); 0
1268 for (const VNInfo *V : ParentLI.valnos) { 0
1269 if (V->isUnused() || !V->isPHIDef()) 0
1270 continue; 0
1271 ----
1272 unsigned RegIdx = RegAssign.lookup(V->def); 0
1273 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
1274 LiveIntervalCalc &LIC = getLICalc(RegIdx); 0
1275 MachineBasicBlock &B = *LIS.getMBBFromIndex(V->def); 0
1276 if (!removeDeadSegment(V->def, LI)) 0
1277 extendPHIRange(B, LIC, LI, LaneBitmask::getAll(), /*Undefs=*/{}); 0
1278 } ----
1279 ----
1280 SmallVector Undefs; 0
1281 LiveIntervalCalc SubLIC; 0
1282 ----
1283 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &PS : ParentLI.subranges()) { 0
1284 for (const VNInfo *V : PS.valnos) { 0
1285 if (V->isUnused() || !V->isPHIDef()) 0
1286 continue; 0
1287 unsigned RegIdx = RegAssign.lookup(V->def); 0
1288 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
1289 LiveInterval::SubRange &S = getSubRangeForMaskExact(PS.LaneMask, LI); 0
1290 if (removeDeadSegment(V->def, S)) 0
1291 continue; 0
1292 ----
1293 MachineBasicBlock &B = *LIS.getMBBFromIndex(V->def); 0
1294 SubLIC.reset(&VRM.getMachineFunction(), LIS.getSlotIndexes(), &MDT, 0
1295 &LIS.getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1296 Undefs.clear(); 0
1297 LI.computeSubRangeUndefs(Undefs, PS.LaneMask, MRI, *LIS.getSlotIndexes()); 0
1298 extendPHIRange(B, SubLIC, S, PS.LaneMask, Undefs); 0
1299 } ----
1300 } ----
1301 } 0
1302 ----
1303 /// rewriteAssigned - Rewrite all uses of Edit->getReg(). ----
1304 void SplitEditor::rewriteAssigned(bool ExtendRanges) { 0
1305 struct ExtPoint { ----
1306 ExtPoint(const MachineOperand &O, unsigned R, SlotIndex N) 0
1307 : MO(O), RegIdx(R), Next(N) {} 0
1308 ----
1309 MachineOperand MO; ----
1310 unsigned RegIdx; ----
1311 SlotIndex Next; ----
1312 }; ----
1313 ----
1314 SmallVector ExtPoints; 0
1315 ----
1316 for (MachineOperand &MO : 0
1317 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.reg_operands(Edit->getReg()))) { 0
1318 MachineInstr *MI = MO.getParent(); 0
1319 // LiveDebugVariables should have handled all DBG_VALUE instructions. ----
1320 if (MI->isDebugValue()) { 0
1321 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Zapping " << *MI); 0
1322 MO.setReg(0); 0
1323 continue; 0
1324 } ----
1325 ----
1326 // operands don't really read the register, so it doesn't matter ----
1327 // which register we choose. When the use operand is tied to a def, we must ----
1328 // use the same register as the def, so just do that always. ----
1329 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*MI); 0
1330 if (MO.isDef() || MO.isUndef()) 0
1331 Idx = Idx.getRegSlot(MO.isEarlyClobber()); 0
1332 ----
1333 // Rewrite to the mapped register at Idx. ----
1334 unsigned RegIdx = RegAssign.lookup(Idx); 0
1335 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(RegIdx)); 0
1336 MO.setReg(LI.reg()); 0
1337 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " rewr " << printMBBReference(*MI->getParent()) 0
1338 << '\t' << Idx << ':' << RegIdx << '\t' << *MI); ----
1339 ----
1340 // Extend liveness to Idx if the instruction reads reg. ----
1341 if (!ExtendRanges || MO.isUndef()) 0
1342 continue; 0
1343 ----
1344 // Skip instructions that don't read Reg. ----
1345 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
1346 if (!MO.getSubReg() && !MO.isEarlyClobber()) 0
1347 continue; 0
1348 // We may want to extend a live range for a partial redef, or for a use ----
1349 // tied to an early clobber. ----
1350 if (!Edit->getParent().liveAt(Idx.getPrevSlot())) 0
1351 continue; 0
1352 } else { ----
1353 assert(MO.isUse()); 0
1354 bool IsEarlyClobber = false; 0
1355 if (MO.isTied()) { 0
1356 // We want to extend a live range into `e` slot rather than `r` slot if ----
1357 // tied-def is early clobber, because the `e` slot already contained ----
1358 // in the live range of early-clobber tied-def operand, give an example ----
1359 // here: ----
1360 // 0 %0 = ... ----
1361 // 16 early-clobber %0 = Op %0 (tied-def 0), ... ----
1362 // 32 ... = Op %0 ----
1363 // Before extend: ----
1364 // %0 = [0r, 0d) [16e, 32d) ----
1365 // The point we want to extend is 0d to 16e not 16r in this case, but if ----
1366 // we use 16r here we will extend nothing because that already contained ----
1367 // in [16e, 32d). ----
1368 unsigned OpIdx = MO.getOperandNo(); 0
1369 unsigned DefOpIdx = MI->findTiedOperandIdx(OpIdx); 0
1370 const MachineOperand &DefOp = MI->getOperand(DefOpIdx); 0
1371 IsEarlyClobber = DefOp.isEarlyClobber(); 0
1372 } ----
1373 ----
1374 Idx = Idx.getRegSlot(IsEarlyClobber); 0
1375 } ----
1376 ----
1377 SlotIndex Next = Idx; 0
1378 if (LI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
1379 // We have to delay extending subranges until we have seen all operands ----
1380 // defining the register. This is because a operand ----
1381 // will create an "undef" point, and we cannot extend any subranges ----
1382 // until all of them have been accounted for. ----
1383 if (MO.isUse()) 0
1384 ExtPoints.push_back(ExtPoint(MO, RegIdx, Next)); 0
1385 } else { ----
1386 LiveIntervalCalc &LIC = getLICalc(RegIdx); 0
1387 LIC.extend(LI, Next, 0, ArrayRef()); 0
1388 } ----
1389 } ----
1390 ----
1391 for (ExtPoint &EP : ExtPoints) { 0
1392 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Edit->get(EP.RegIdx)); 0
1393 assert(LI.hasSubRanges()); 0
1394 ----
1395 LiveIntervalCalc SubLIC; 0
1396 Register Reg = EP.MO.getReg(), Sub = EP.MO.getSubReg(); 0
1397 LaneBitmask LM = Sub != 0 ? TRI.getSubRegIndexLaneMask(Sub) 0
1398 : MRI.getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(Reg); 0
1399 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
1400 if ((S.LaneMask & LM).none()) 0
1401 continue; 0
1402 // The problem here can be that the new register may have been created ----
1403 // for a partially defined original register. For example: ----
1404 // %0:subreg_hireg = ... ----
1405 // ... ----
1406 // %1 = COPY %0 ----
1407 if (S.empty()) 0
1408 continue; 0
1409 SubLIC.reset(&VRM.getMachineFunction(), LIS.getSlotIndexes(), &MDT, 0
1410 &LIS.getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1411 SmallVector Undefs; 0
1412 LI.computeSubRangeUndefs(Undefs, S.LaneMask, MRI, *LIS.getSlotIndexes()); 0
1413 SubLIC.extend(S, EP.Next, 0, Undefs); 0
1414 } 0
1415 } 0
1416 ----
1417 for (Register R : *Edit) { 0
1418 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(R); 0
1419 if (!LI.hasSubRanges()) 0
1420 continue; 0
1421 LI.clear(); 0
1422 LI.removeEmptySubRanges(); 0
1423 LIS.constructMainRangeFromSubranges(LI); 0
1424 } ----
1425 } 0
1426 ----
1427 void SplitEditor::deleteRematVictims() { 0
1428 SmallVector Dead; 0
1429 for (const Register &R : *Edit) { 0
1430 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(R); 0
1431 for (const LiveRange::Segment &S : LI->segments) { 0
1432 // Dead defs end at the dead slot. ----
1433 if (S.end != S.valno->def.getDeadSlot()) 0
1434 continue; 0
1435 if (S.valno->isPHIDef()) 0
1436 continue; 0
1437 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(S.valno->def); 0
1438 assert(MI && "Missing instruction for dead def"); 0
1439 MI->addRegisterDead(LI->reg(), &TRI); 0
1440 ----
1441 if (!MI->allDefsAreDead()) 0
1442 continue; 0
1443 ----
1444 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "All defs dead: " << *MI); 0
1445 Dead.push_back(MI); 0
1446 } ----
1447 } ----
1448 ----
1449 if (Dead.empty()) 0
1450 return; 0
1451 ----
1452 Edit->eliminateDeadDefs(Dead, std::nullopt); 0
1453 } 0
1454 ----
1455 void SplitEditor::forceRecomputeVNI(const VNInfo &ParentVNI) { 0
1456 // Fast-path for common case. ----
1457 if (!ParentVNI.isPHIDef()) { 0
1458 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Edit->size(); I != E; ++I) 0
1459 forceRecompute(I, ParentVNI); 0
1460 return; 0
1461 } ----
1462 ----
1463 // Trace value through phis. ----
1464 SmallPtrSet Visited; ///< whether VNI was/is in worklist. 0
1465 SmallVector WorkList; 0
1466 Visited.insert(&ParentVNI); 0
1467 WorkList.push_back(&ParentVNI); 0
1468 ----
1469 const LiveInterval &ParentLI = Edit->getParent(); 0
1470 const SlotIndexes &Indexes = *LIS.getSlotIndexes(); 0
1471 do { ----
1472 const VNInfo &VNI = *WorkList.back(); 0
1473 WorkList.pop_back(); 0
1474 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Edit->size(); I != E; ++I) 0
1475 forceRecompute(I, VNI); 0
1476 if (!VNI.isPHIDef()) 0
1477 continue; 0
1478 ----
1479 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *Indexes.getMBBFromIndex(VNI.def); 0
1480 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
1481 SlotIndex PredEnd = Indexes.getMBBEndIdx(Pred); 0
1482 VNInfo *PredVNI = ParentLI.getVNInfoBefore(PredEnd); 0
1483 assert(PredVNI && "Value available in PhiVNI predecessor"); 0
1484 if (Visited.insert(PredVNI).second) 0
1485 WorkList.push_back(PredVNI); 0
1486 } ----
1487 } while(!WorkList.empty()); 0
1488 } 0
1489 ----
1490 void SplitEditor::finish(SmallVectorImpl *LRMap) { 0
1491 ++NumFinished; 0
1492 ----
1493 // At this point, the live intervals in Edit contain VNInfos corresponding to ----
1494 // the inserted copies. ----
1495 ----
1496 // Add the original defs from the parent interval. ----
1497 for (const VNInfo *ParentVNI : Edit->getParent().valnos) { 0
1498 if (ParentVNI->isUnused()) 0
1499 continue; 0
1500 unsigned RegIdx = RegAssign.lookup(ParentVNI->def); 0
1501 defValue(RegIdx, ParentVNI, ParentVNI->def, true); 0
1502 ----
1503 // Force rematted values to be recomputed everywhere. ----
1504 // The new live ranges may be truncated. ----
1505 if (Edit->didRematerialize(ParentVNI)) 0
1506 forceRecomputeVNI(*ParentVNI); 0
1507 } ----
1508 ----
1509 // Hoist back-copies to the complement interval when in spill mode. ----
1510 switch (SpillMode) { 0
1511 case SM_Partition: 0
1512 // Leave all back-copies as is. ----
1513 break; 0
1514 case SM_Size: 0
1515 case SM_Speed: ----
1516 // hoistCopies will behave differently between size and speed. ----
1517 hoistCopies(); 0
1518 } ----
1519 ----
1520 // Transfer the simply mapped values, check if any are skipped. ----
1521 bool Skipped = transferValues(); 0
1522 ----
1523 // Rewrite virtual registers, possibly extending ranges. ----
1524 rewriteAssigned(Skipped); 0
1525 ----
1526 if (Skipped) 0
1527 extendPHIKillRanges(); 0
1528 else ----
1529 ++NumSimple; 0
1530 ----
1531 // Delete defs that were rematted everywhere. ----
1532 if (Skipped) 0
1533 deleteRematVictims(); 0
1534 ----
1535 // Get rid of unused values and set phi-kill flags. ----
1536 for (Register Reg : *Edit) { 0
1537 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Reg); 0
1538 LI.removeEmptySubRanges(); 0
1539 LI.RenumberValues(); 0
1540 } ----
1541 ----
1542 // Provide a reverse mapping from original indices to Edit ranges. ----
1543 if (LRMap) { 0
1544 auto Seq = llvm::seq(0, Edit->size()); 0
1545 LRMap->assign(Seq.begin(), Seq.end()); 0
1546 } ----
1547 ----
1548 // Now check if any registers were separated into multiple components. ----
1549 ConnectedVNInfoEqClasses ConEQ(LIS); 0
1550 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Edit->size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1551 // Don't use iterators, they are invalidated by create() below. ----
1552 Register VReg = Edit->get(i); 0
1553 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(VReg); 0
1554 SmallVector SplitLIs; 0
1555 LIS.splitSeparateComponents(LI, SplitLIs); 0
1556 Register Original = VRM.getOriginal(VReg); 0
1557 for (LiveInterval *SplitLI : SplitLIs) 0
1558 VRM.setIsSplitFromReg(SplitLI->reg(), Original); 0
1559 ----
1560 // The new intervals all map back to i. ----
1561 if (LRMap) 0
1562 LRMap->resize(Edit->size(), i); 0
1563 } 0
1564 ----
1565 // Calculate spill weight and allocation hints for new intervals. ----
1566 Edit->calculateRegClassAndHint(VRM.getMachineFunction(), VRAI); 0
1567 ----
1568 assert(!LRMap || LRMap->size() == Edit->size()); 0
1569 } 0
1570 ----
1571 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1572 // Single Block Splitting ----
1573 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1574 ----
1575 bool SplitAnalysis::shouldSplitSingleBlock(const BlockInfo &BI, 0
1576 bool SingleInstrs) const { ----
1577 // Always split for multiple instructions. ----
1578 if (!BI.isOneInstr()) 0
1579 return true; 0
1580 // Don't split for single instructions unless explicitly requested. ----
1581 if (!SingleInstrs) 0
1582 return false; 0
1583 // Splitting a live-through range always makes progress. ----
1584 if (BI.LiveIn && BI.LiveOut) 0
1585 return true; 0
1586 // No point in isolating a copy. It has no register class constraints. ----
1587 if (LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(BI.FirstInstr)->isCopyLike()) 0
1588 return false; 0
1589 // Finally, don't isolate an end point that was created by earlier splits. ----
1590 return isOriginalEndpoint(BI.FirstInstr); 0
1591 } ----
1592 ----
1593 void SplitEditor::splitSingleBlock(const SplitAnalysis::BlockInfo &BI) { 0
1594 openIntv(); 0
1595 SlotIndex LastSplitPoint = SA.getLastSplitPoint(BI.MBB); 0
1596 SlotIndex SegStart = enterIntvBefore(std::min(BI.FirstInstr, 0
1597 LastSplitPoint)); ----
1598 if (!BI.LiveOut || BI.LastInstr < LastSplitPoint) { 0
1599 useIntv(SegStart, leaveIntvAfter(BI.LastInstr)); 0
1600 } else { ----
1601 // The last use is after the last valid split point. ----
1602 SlotIndex SegStop = leaveIntvBefore(LastSplitPoint); 0
1603 useIntv(SegStart, SegStop); 0
1604 overlapIntv(SegStop, BI.LastInstr); 0
1605 } ----
1606 } 0
1607 ----
1608 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1609 // Global Live Range Splitting Support ----
1610 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1611 ----
1612 // These methods support a method of global live range splitting that uses a ----
1613 // global algorithm to decide intervals for CFG edges. They will insert split ----
1614 // points and color intervals in basic blocks while avoiding interference. ----
1615 // ----
1616 // Note that splitSingleBlock is also useful for blocks where both CFG edges ----
1617 // are on the stack. ----
1618 ----
1619 void SplitEditor::splitLiveThroughBlock(unsigned MBBNum, 0
1620 unsigned IntvIn, SlotIndex LeaveBefore, ----
1621 unsigned IntvOut, SlotIndex EnterAfter){ ----
1622 SlotIndex Start, Stop; 0
1623 std::tie(Start, Stop) = LIS.getSlotIndexes()->getMBBRange(MBBNum); 0
1624 ----
1625 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "%bb." << MBBNum << " [" << Start << ';' << Stop 0
1626 << ") intf " << LeaveBefore << '-' << EnterAfter ----
1627 << ", live-through " << IntvIn << " -> " << IntvOut); ----
1628 ----
1629 assert((IntvIn || IntvOut) && "Use splitSingleBlock for isolated blocks"); 0
1630 ----
1631 assert((!LeaveBefore || LeaveBefore < Stop) && "Interference after block"); 0
1632 assert((!IntvIn || !LeaveBefore || LeaveBefore > Start) && "Impossible intf"); 0
1633 assert((!EnterAfter || EnterAfter >= Start) && "Interference before block"); 0
1634 ----
1635 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = VRM.getMachineFunction().getBlockNumbered(MBBNum); 0
1636 ----
1637 if (!IntvOut) { 0
1638 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ", spill on entry.\n"); 0
1639 // ----
1640 // <<<<<<<<< Possible LeaveBefore interference. ----
1641 // |-----------| Live through. ----
1642 // -____________ Spill on entry. ----
1643 // ----
1644 selectIntv(IntvIn); 0
1645 SlotIndex Idx = leaveIntvAtTop(*MBB); 0
1646 assert((!LeaveBefore || Idx <= LeaveBefore) && "Interference"); 0
1647 (void)Idx; ----
1648 return; 0
1649 } ----
1650 ----
1651 if (!IntvIn) { 0
1652 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ", reload on exit.\n"); 0
1653 // ----
1654 // >>>>>>> Possible EnterAfter interference. ----
1655 // |-----------| Live through. ----
1656 // ___________-- Reload on exit. ----
1657 // ----
1658 selectIntv(IntvOut); 0
1659 SlotIndex Idx = enterIntvAtEnd(*MBB); 0
1660 assert((!EnterAfter || Idx >= EnterAfter) && "Interference"); 0
1661 (void)Idx; ----
1662 return; 0
1663 } ----
1664 ----
1665 if (IntvIn == IntvOut && !LeaveBefore && !EnterAfter) { 0
1666 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ", straight through.\n"); 0
1667 // ----
1668 // |-----------| Live through. ----
1669 // ------------- Straight through, same intv, no interference. ----
1670 // ----
1671 selectIntv(IntvOut); 0
1672 useIntv(Start, Stop); 0
1673 return; 0
1674 } ----
1675 ----
1676 // We cannot legally insert splits after LSP. ----
1677 SlotIndex LSP = SA.getLastSplitPoint(MBBNum); 0
1678 assert((!IntvOut || !EnterAfter || EnterAfter < LSP) && "Impossible intf"); 0
1679 ----
1680 if (IntvIn != IntvOut && (!LeaveBefore || !EnterAfter || 0
1681 LeaveBefore.getBaseIndex() > EnterAfter.getBoundaryIndex())) { 0
1682 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ", switch avoiding interference.\n"); 0
1683 // ----
1684 // >>>> <<<< Non-overlapping EnterAfter/LeaveBefore interference. ----
1685 // |-----------| Live through. ----
1686 // ------======= Switch intervals between interference. ----
1687 // ----
1688 selectIntv(IntvOut); 0
1689 SlotIndex Idx; 0
1690 if (LeaveBefore && LeaveBefore < LSP) { 0
1691 Idx = enterIntvBefore(LeaveBefore); 0
1692 useIntv(Idx, Stop); 0
1693 } else { ----
1694 Idx = enterIntvAtEnd(*MBB); 0
1695 } ----
1696 selectIntv(IntvIn); 0
